President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has ordered that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff as a mark of respect for the victims of the violent acts that occurred on May 26, 2021, in San Jose, California. This order applies to the White House, public buildings and grounds, military posts, naval stations, naval vessels, and all federal government facilities in the District of Columbia, the United States, its territories, and possessions until sunset on May 30, 2021. The flag will also be flown at half-staff for the same duration at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations. The order was issued on May 26, 2021.